  "number": 1296,
  "html_url": "https://github.com/algolia/instantsearch/issues/1296",
  "title": "Synchronizing state of widgets that share the same attribute name ",
  "body": "Currently widgets that share the same attribute name doesn't share the same state. It means that if a user has two widgets for the same refinement, there will not be synchronized. \n\nExample : on the e-commerce demo we have two widgets to refine on prices. If the user selects a range on the prices list, the input range will not be automatically synchronized. Same thing for the url.\n\nOne solution would be that when the store is updated, widgets that share the same attribute name as the one that is responsible for the update, would have their state automatically changed as well. \nBut this synchronization is currently not that simple because widgets doesn't necessarily share the same internal state. \n\nex: taking the e-commerce demo again, for displaying prices, we use NumericRefinementList and InputRange widgets. The first one uses a \"min:max\" string as its internal, the seconde one uses an object with min/max values. \n\n@Morhaus  : when developing react-instantsearch, have you thought about this problematic and already have some ideas about it ? \n",
  "created_at": "2016-09-19T11:29:43Z",
